750ml = about 25 oz.

I don't carbonate this way, but if someone says that amount of sugar
(a teaspoon) works well for 12 oz, maybe you should consider doubling
it for 25 oz (or use prime tabs and follow the instructions).

Mixing sugar with the whole batch first is more accurate if you are
able to do it. You don't do it in the fermenter, but in another vessel
used specifically to hold the racked beer from the fermenter to bottle
it. Boil the sugar in a little water and dump it in the sanitized
bucket, then rack your beer into it. Stir a little (don't airate) and
bottle from there. One of my recipes says 3/4 cup of corn sugar for a
5.5 gallon batch. Table sugar will work just as well, however it
measures differently, so let someone else provide opinion on how much
to use. Measuring by weight is far more accurate.

