Secondary fermentation is where you transfer from primary after initial
fermentation into another container and let it sit longer before bottling.
Depending on the style it could sit in secondary for months not weeks. This
helps with aging and clarity of the beer. You can find more about
secondaries in &quot;How To Brew.&quot;

Because your beer tends to sit longer in secondary and it produces less CO2
it is more important to have a fairly air tight container and one with a
