Secondaries are optional, but the general idea is that you leave the beer in
the primary fermenter until the majority of activity is over.  Then you
rack the beer over to the secondary fermenter so that it has time to finish
and settle/clear away from the trub (aka grey gunge).  Then after it's been
in the secondary for however long you want, you rack it to the bottling
bucket.

It varies a lot based on the beer, but in general my schedule is about a week
in the primary, two weeks in the secondary, and then about a week to carbonate.

John.
